---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Justin Doone"
  description="15+ years marketing complex products in financial services and complex B2B. Hong Kong, Toronto, and now Evolve ETFs."
>
  <!-- HERO (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative pt-24 md:pt-36 pb-12 md:pb-16">
    <div class="hero-orb hero-orb-a" style="top: -10%; right: -15%;"></div>
    <div
      class="hero-orb hero-orb-b"
      style="bottom: -25%; left: 0%; opacity: 0.25; background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-accent-cool), transparent 60%);"
    ></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <img
        src="/images/profile.jpg"
        alt="Justin Doone"
        width="200"
        height="200"
        class="hero-line w-36 h-36 md:w-44 md:h-44 rounded-full object-cover mb-10 ring-1 ring-on-dark-mute"
        data-line="0"
      />
      <p class="hero-line eyebrow mb-8" data-line="0">About</p>
      <h1
        class="hero-line heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-10 leading-[0.95]"
        data-line="1"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        15+ years marketing products that take <em style="color: var(--color-accent); font-style: italic;">explaining</em>.
      </h1>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6"
        data-line="2"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        Mostly financial services and complex B2B. Started in Hong Kong on the agency side of financial communications, then in-house IR, then marketing for a pan-Asian real estate developer. Moved to Toronto for real estate PE/AM at Greybrook and Clifton Blake. Currently at Evolve ETFs, running digital marketing for a 41-fund lineup.
      </p>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-lg leading-relaxed"
        data-line="3"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        Mostly lean teams. More of the marketing function on me than the title would suggest, and more tooling I've built because off-the-shelf didn't fit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK (dark, continued) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-16 md:py-20" data-reveal>
    <div
      class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 rule-top pt-16"
    >
      <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
      <div
        class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-lg"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          On lean teams the same desk owns the work from copy through to analytics, including the conversations with compliance about what you can actually say. Strategy gets sharper when the person briefing the campaign is the same person reading the numbers later.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          I build small tools for the team because off-the-shelf usually doesn't fit. Reporting consolidations, competitive-intel pipelines, automation for the recurring chores, and ad-hoc diagnostics. AI assist makes that possible in days, which used to take a quarter of engineering bandwidth to get scheduled.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
          Most of my work has been in regulated industries. You learn to write copy with legal in mind from the first draft, since skipping that step usually means launching a quarter late after compliance kicks it back. Copy has to land legally before it can land persuasively, and that's a skill that travels to any category with the same kind of review.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-24 md:py-32" data-reveal>
    <div class="hero-orb" style="top: 0%; right: -10%; opacity: 0.3;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
      <h2
        class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        Tell me what you're trying to ship.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="mailto:justindoone@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent-warm transition-colors"
      >
        justindoone@gmail.com
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
